content.description: Follow some horizontal cracks to the first roof.  The center section has some great off balance movement that will test your body position.  Finish on easier rock after another small roof.  The finish requires some gear.  My partner placed a blue offset nut and a green alien.
content.location: Middle of the three routes between Darth Vader and We Free Again Boys...

content.description: This is a fun looong 5.10 route, which goes for a full 60M.  Pull a low roof and follow some interesting face climbing to the roof crux.  Follow easier rock to the anchors.  The final roof has some lichen, which will make things interesting with 40M of rope out. Rap twice or once with 2 ropes...
content.location: Rightmost route through a left angling roof system 20ft off the ground.

content.description:
Classic creative slab and face climbing that engages from bottom to top.

Starts in a thin short dihedral past 2 bolts, and then up the steep slabs to a small left facing and leaning book before busting back right over a bulge to the finish. The left facing book is obvious from the ground.
content.protection: 14 draws, one .5 camalot protects a small 5.9 runout
content.location: On the left side of the Dark Side just before the base of the dome starts plating as it runs into Shape Shifter.

content.description:
Another tricky and engaging face climb at the Dark Side.  Start near the left end of the cliff at a left facing corner feature.  Trend up and right through varied face climbing to a difficult lieback feature going back left.  Ten bolts and thirty meters to a two-bolt anchor with rings.

There is also a second pitch, supposedly 10b and another thirty meters to the top, but it didn't seem like this got done much.  The first pitch makes for for an excellent single pitch climb.
content.location: This climb is near the left end of the cliff.  It is number 3 in the Graham Doe guidebook.  See picture for the precise start.

content.description: bolted  face climb, hard to find first bolt. With Book look where line goes[ leaning left ] , because it had to find camouflage bolts while climbing

Poor holds right off the ground lead to steep moves on good holds past the first bolt. (Stick clip useful). Romp up to the 3rd bolt and get a good rest. The fixed nut is pretty good and can be backed up with a .5 camalot or 1-1.5" piece. Fight up the overhanging layback to a stance and a bolt. Work left on good holds to a nice rest. Quest up the face past a mix of bolts and gear until you make it to a roof way up high. Pull another solid 5.11/11+ crux past closely spaced bolts. Some more easy climbing, and a few tricky hero moves lead to an anchor at 35 meters. Watch the end of your rope if you lower off!
content.protection: 13 Bolts plus a single set of cams to 2.5". Bolted anchor with Chains. Makes sure you have a 70m rope. Otherwise rappel to the right to the midway anchor on Welcome to the Darkside.
content.location: This route is under a nice roof and the lefmost of a trio of bolt lines (Welcome to Darkside, We Free Boys). Look for a low roof and then a fin of rock on the right of a second roof about 20 feet up.

content.protection: 10 bolts, gear to 3". Chain Anchor. Gear protects the lowest section before the first (high) bolt. Few other placements can be found higher up. Given the zig-zag nature of the climb, use long slings to extend the draws and your placements to avoid rope drag.
content.location: Climbs the obvious dihedral up to a big roof. The climbs got around the roof (right) and finishes up the featured face.

content.description:
Pitch One: Start at a steep roof, pulling hard moves to get past it. Fun and balancy 5.11 climbing leads to the next roof. Easier climbing to the anchor. 13 bolts runnout at the end can be protected with small/medium gear. 12a/b

Pitch Two: Fun mostly easy climbing for another 100'. 6 bolts with longish runnouts over very easy terrain, optional small/medium cams. 5.10a

Originally Done as one 60m pitch.
content.protection:
Bolts. optional small/medium cams to protect easy runnout sections.

Be extremely careful rapping with a 60m rope
content.location: Starts about 20 left of Darth Vadar at the low roof.
